.** \n.\n.\nI swabbed the surfaces before cleaning, and then used the spray bottle, which generates #aqueousozone on demand, waited 30 seconds, and wiped. I swabbed the clean surfaces, and transferred those samples to the agar plates. This video shows my results 3 days later. \ud83e\udd17\n\nAqueous ozone works as a powerful sanitizer, deodorizer, and cleaner - all you need is tap water and electricity. **No cartridges or capsules**. After it\u2019s done kicking some serious bacteria booty, it converts back into water and oxygen, making it a safe, non-toxic cleaning solution for any household. \n.\nAqueous ozone also isn\u2019t NEW. Ozone water treatment has been used commercially since 1904, and is still used today. But, the proof is in the pudding, so I put this video together showing how well it worked in our house \ud83d\udc4f. \nThis cleaner has also been shown to demonstrate greater than 99.9% inactivation of Human Coronavirus \n229E/ATCC VR-740, a commercially available surrogate virus for the Human Coronavirus SARS-Cov-2 which causes the COVID-19 Disease within 30 seconds \ud83e\udda0 \ud83d\ude4c\nFull review: SLAYathomemother.com/cleaning-with-ozonated-water\nSpray bottle: @o3waterworks", "commentsCount": 99, "commentsDisabled": false, "dimensionsHeight": 1333, "dimensionsWidth": 750, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-lga3-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/643047339_899135706265222_4572540157160897162_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=110&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gH9SpdXHWjF8CxlnE4u2D_6lwvd5VT6xcbFSdFTqGAO8Hu0rfUoOgrwIn5XaO7cj80&_nc_ohc=dK67WOBxHagQ7kNvwE6tEqA&_nc_gid=KbBg7lTCu4yJfIIcB9CsCg&edm=AOQ1c0wBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQB4xjBzKSEa8UFzoNi8xXOh0-k2Kas8Sj74xDKQ89bJyw&oe=6A628F3B&_nc_sid=8b3546", "likesCount": 230, "videoDuration": 176.2, "videoViewCount": 3416, "id": "2457120414783126415", "hashtags": ["beforeandafter", "aqueousozone"], "mentions": ["o3waterworks"], "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/CIZcf-1gjuP/", "firstComment":